1
00:00:02,000 --> 00:00:04,067
- [SCREAMS]
<i> - Raphie!</i>

2
00:00:04,633 --> 00:00:05,567
<i> Shh!</i>

3
00:00:05,733 --> 00:00:07,900
<i>Sir Martin told me to
keep an eye on you guys.</i>

4
00:00:08,100 --> 00:00:10,400
<i>You're not going to tell
our brothers, right?</i>

5
00:00:10,500 --> 00:00:11,933
<i> Girl, I can't do that.</i>

6
00:00:12,100 --> 00:00:13,633
<i> My charm works on Sir Kiko.</i>

7
00:00:13,800 --> 00:00:15,067
<i> But Sir Martin?</i>

8
00:00:15,167 --> 00:00:17,267
<i>We'd be dead.
He'd scold us for sure!</i>

9
00:00:17,433 --> 00:00:19,400
<i>What we're doing
is for our families...</i>

10
00:00:19,933 --> 00:00:21,633
<i> Mm-hm?</i>

11
00:00:21,800 --> 00:00:23,400
<i> Thank you so much!</i>

12
00:00:23,500 --> 00:00:24,700
[PHONE RINGING]

13
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:26,133
<i> This is Kiko.</i>

14
00:00:26,300 --> 00:00:27,600
<i> Meet me.</i>

15
00:00:27,767 --> 00:00:29,433
<i> The numbers, the coordinates?</i>

16
00:00:29,600 --> 00:00:32,733
<i>The treasure was hidden
here on our island.</i>

17
00:00:32,833 --> 00:00:34,267
<i> Mount Arelag!</i>

18
00:00:34,433 --> 00:00:37,900
<i>And that's what you need
to find, Martin.</i>

19
00:00:42,467 --> 00:00:48,833
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

20
00:00:49,633 --> 00:00:50,900
I need to talk to Jade.

21
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:52,967
Edward, you know
that's not possible.

22
00:00:53,633 --> 00:00:55,000
Maybe you can help me out, Kiko.

23
00:00:55,167 --> 00:00:57,267
And make her siblings
mad at me?

24
00:00:57,867 --> 00:01:00,167
Just for a moment.
I need to talk to her.

25
00:01:00,333 --> 00:01:03,133
Why can't you respect
her family's wishes?

26
00:01:03,300 --> 00:01:05,567
What matters to me
is how Jade sees me.

27
00:01:05,667 --> 00:01:06,900
If she's not mad at me,

28
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:08,333
I won't stop trying
to talk to her.

29
00:01:08,533 --> 00:01:10,167
Edward, Jade already
has enough problems.

30
00:01:10,333 --> 00:01:12,633
- You're making it worse.
- That's none of your business!

31
00:01:12,733 --> 00:01:15,333
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

32
00:01:15,467 --> 00:01:17,167
You think I don't know
what you're doing?

33
00:01:17,300 --> 00:01:19,167
I'm not doing anything wrong.

34
00:01:19,867 --> 00:01:21,300
Really?

35
00:01:22,200 --> 00:01:24,500
You like Jade, that's why
you're acting like this.

36
00:01:25,067 --> 00:01:26,367
We're friends.

37
00:01:27,567 --> 00:01:28,933
[EDWARD] Really?

38
00:01:30,333 --> 00:01:31,867
You're just taking
advantage of the fact

39
00:01:32,033 --> 00:01:33,633
that her family kept us apart.

40
00:01:33,900 --> 00:01:35,133
[SCOFFS]

41
00:01:35,900 --> 00:01:37,800
You're selfish too,
you know that?

42
00:01:37,900 --> 00:01:41,000
I asked you to come here so
I could tell you to your face

43
00:01:41,200 --> 00:01:43,200
that every time you force
yourself into talking to her,

44
00:01:43,367 --> 00:01:45,033
Jade's the one who suffers.

45
00:01:45,833 --> 00:01:49,067
Her siblings always lecture her
whenever you come up.

46
00:01:49,233 --> 00:01:50,700
Do you think it's easy for Jade

47
00:01:50,867 --> 00:01:52,367
to be fighting with her
own siblings?

48
00:01:54,900 --> 00:01:56,300
I never wanted that.

49
00:01:56,733 --> 00:01:58,533
If you really care about her,

50
00:01:58,667 --> 00:02:00,700
you'd think about
the situation she's in.

51
00:02:00,833 --> 00:02:05,567
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

52
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:20,600
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

53
00:03:15,167 --> 00:03:18,633
[PHONE RINGING]

54
00:03:19,833 --> 00:03:21,067
Hello, Mom?

55
00:03:21,200 --> 00:03:23,267
[FRIDA] Thank God you answered.

56
00:03:23,767 --> 00:03:25,133
<i> Sweetie, where are you?</i>

57
00:03:25,767 --> 00:03:26,733
Uh...

58
00:03:26,833 --> 00:03:29,000
I'm here at the hotel. Why?

59
00:03:29,933 --> 00:03:31,667
[FRIDA] Are you with Luna?

60
00:03:32,200 --> 00:03:33,733
<i> I can't contact them.</i>

61
00:03:33,833 --> 00:03:35,433
Uh...

62
00:03:35,533 --> 00:03:39,333
Mom, remember there's a
dead spot here in the hotel?

63
00:03:40,667 --> 00:03:42,100
Maybe she's there.

64
00:03:42,200 --> 00:03:44,133
She's probably fixing
something out back.

65
00:03:45,033 --> 00:03:46,500
<i> And your brother?</i>

66
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:51,067
You know Justin.

67
00:03:51,167 --> 00:03:53,767
He probably just went out
with his friends.

68
00:03:54,867 --> 00:03:56,767
<i> Okay, take care over there.</i>

69
00:03:57,867 --> 00:03:58,800
Okay, Mom.

70
00:03:59,467 --> 00:04:00,533
Love you.

71
00:04:01,333 --> 00:04:02,867
[KIKO] Who was that?

72
00:04:03,033 --> 00:04:04,533
Uh, Mom.

73
00:04:04,700 --> 00:04:07,700
She was just asking me
about Luna and Justin.

74
00:04:08,733 --> 00:04:09,933
What did you tell her?

75
00:04:10,733 --> 00:04:13,200
I told her Luna was fixing
some stuff.

76
00:04:13,367 --> 00:04:15,167
And Justin just went out.

77
00:04:17,733 --> 00:04:18,667
You?

78
00:04:19,300 --> 00:04:20,600
Where did you come from?

79
00:04:21,167 --> 00:04:22,500
Uh...

80
00:04:22,667 --> 00:04:23,667
Just around.

81
00:04:23,800 --> 00:04:25,700
I just handled something
with housekeeping.

82
00:04:27,567 --> 00:04:28,833
Jade.

83
00:04:29,400 --> 00:04:32,133
Maybe we should continue this
some other time.

84
00:04:32,233 --> 00:04:33,800
It's better if you head
home now.

85
00:04:34,533 --> 00:04:35,367
Huh?

86
00:04:35,533 --> 00:04:37,867
Kiko, I'm okay.
I can keep going.

87
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:40,067
You're tired.
You already fell asleep.

88
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:43,667
Come on, I'll take you home.
I'll take care of the book.

89
00:04:44,733 --> 00:04:46,033
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

90
00:04:46,167 --> 00:04:47,833
So that's why you haven't
been reaching out.

91
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:51,667
I had no one else to contact
to get a message to you.

92
00:04:52,500 --> 00:04:54,400
What kind of help do you need?

93
00:04:55,567 --> 00:04:57,367
I still haven't paid you back.

94
00:04:58,567 --> 00:05:00,667
You already paid me
more than enough back then.

95
00:05:02,967 --> 00:05:04,600
Just tell me, Leon.

96
00:05:05,633 --> 00:05:08,833
Do you want me to investigate
who put the body in your car?

97
00:05:10,200 --> 00:05:11,233
Yeah.

98
00:05:11,567 --> 00:05:13,367
That could help with my case.

99
00:05:13,800 --> 00:05:15,400
[SCOFFS] That's easy then.

100
00:05:17,200 --> 00:05:18,933
I'll give you Luna's number.

101
00:05:19,633 --> 00:05:21,533
She's the one you should call
if something happens.

102
00:05:26,133 --> 00:05:31,733
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

103
00:05:32,367 --> 00:05:33,600
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

104
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:35,600
I think we're safe.

105
00:05:36,300 --> 00:05:37,567
What do you mean safe?

106
00:05:37,667 --> 00:05:39,700
We'd be safer if we just
went home.

107
00:05:40,400 --> 00:05:42,300
[CLANKING DISTANTLY]

108
00:05:42,467 --> 00:05:45,800
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

109
00:05:47,800 --> 00:05:50,600
[INDISTINCT CHATTERING]

110
00:05:51,767 --> 00:05:52,900
Get the drinks!

111
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:54,267
So, is she coming?

112
00:05:54,400 --> 00:05:56,067
- She's coming.
- Yeah.

113
00:05:56,167 --> 00:05:57,600
- Relax.
- Just wait.

114
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:01,567
She'll come. Relax.

115
00:06:02,633 --> 00:06:04,867
I'm getting impatient,
I just want my cash!

116
00:06:05,767 --> 00:06:07,367
Just wait, relax.

117
00:06:07,500 --> 00:06:09,300
[TRIXIE] Cheska.
That guy over there,

118
00:06:09,467 --> 00:06:10,967
he's the one who kidnapped Juan.

119
00:06:11,133 --> 00:06:12,167
- What?
- That's him.

120
00:06:12,333 --> 00:06:13,733
- Are you sure?
- Yes!

121
00:06:13,833 --> 00:06:14,967
Are you sure she's coming?

122
00:06:15,133 --> 00:06:16,833
She'll show up.

123
00:06:17,533 --> 00:06:20,167
That means they came back here
even after Juan died.

124
00:06:20,333 --> 00:06:23,800
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

125
00:06:23,967 --> 00:06:25,333
- [WOMAN] Here.
- Boss!

126
00:06:25,500 --> 00:06:27,400
I kept my promise to you, okay?

127
00:06:29,767 --> 00:06:30,733
A woman?

128
00:06:31,467 --> 00:06:32,900
They have a female accomplice!

129
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:34,467
What? A woman?

130
00:06:35,167 --> 00:06:36,567
It sounds...

131
00:06:37,267 --> 00:06:39,300
It sounds like I've heard
that voice before.

132
00:06:39,633 --> 00:06:41,300
- Check it.
- Go on, take a peek.

133
00:06:41,467 --> 00:06:43,133
No way. I'm not peeking.

134
00:06:43,233 --> 00:06:47,667
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

135
00:06:47,833 --> 00:06:48,867
[MARINA] Here.

136
00:06:50,467 --> 00:06:52,600
- Wow!
- That's a lot!

137
00:06:53,200 --> 00:06:54,433
[GASPS]

138
00:06:55,867 --> 00:06:57,133
- Why?
- She's the cop!

139
00:06:57,233 --> 00:06:58,433
- The cop!
- What?

140
00:06:58,533 --> 00:07:01,600
[MARINA] Maybe next time,
Boss will hand you even more.

141
00:07:03,033 --> 00:07:04,100
Everything's settled, Boss!

142
00:07:04,200 --> 00:07:06,433
[GOONS GIGGLING]

143
00:07:06,533 --> 00:07:08,333
- Hey! Hey!
- Cheska, stop it!

144
00:07:08,500 --> 00:07:09,833
Raphie, what are you...

145
00:07:10,900 --> 00:07:11,933
[THUDS]

146
00:07:14,933 --> 00:07:15,867
[GUN COCKS]

147
00:07:18,700 --> 00:07:25,700
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

148
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:49,867
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

149
00:08:04,600 --> 00:08:11,667
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

150
00:08:21,100 --> 00:08:22,067
[VITO] He's alive.

151
00:08:24,333 --> 00:08:26,567
<i> He's here on the island.</i>

152
00:08:26,667 --> 00:08:33,733
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

153
00:08:43,600 --> 00:08:50,633
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

154
00:08:53,300 --> 00:08:55,767
[PHONE RINGING]

155
00:08:55,967 --> 00:08:57,067
S-Sorry!

156
00:08:57,167 --> 00:08:58,433
[RINGING CONTINUES]

157
00:08:59,333 --> 00:09:01,967
[THUDS]

158
00:09:02,133 --> 00:09:08,967
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

159
00:09:11,167 --> 00:09:12,400
Nothing.

160
00:09:13,767 --> 00:09:14,767
Come on.

161
00:09:22,167 --> 00:09:23,400
[SIGHS IN RELIEF]

162
00:09:24,967 --> 00:09:28,967
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

163
00:09:31,300 --> 00:09:32,467
Let's go.

164
00:09:33,200 --> 00:09:34,667
- Let's go.
- Come on.

165
00:09:44,867 --> 00:09:46,667
Let's go.

166
00:09:49,733 --> 00:09:51,700
- [VITO]<i> I can't be wrong.
</i>- [LINE RINGING]

167
00:09:51,867 --> 00:09:54,000
<i> - That was Sandro Soliman.
</i>- [BEEPING]

168
00:09:56,867 --> 00:09:58,700
<i> Leon needs to know about this.</i>

169
00:09:59,467 --> 00:10:02,000
He needs to know Sandro's alive.

170
00:10:02,167 --> 00:10:03,700
[LINE RINGING]

171
00:10:07,367 --> 00:10:09,633
[LINE RINGING]

172
00:10:12,333 --> 00:10:17,400
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

173
00:10:17,567 --> 00:10:19,833
[LINE RINGING]

174
00:10:19,933 --> 00:10:21,567
[PHONE RINGING]

175
00:10:21,733 --> 00:10:23,833
- [LUNA] Who is this?
- [RINGING CONTINUES]

176
00:10:23,933 --> 00:10:26,167
[GIO] Who keeps calling?
It's been ringing nonstop.

177
00:10:26,700 --> 00:10:28,567
I honestly don't know.

178
00:10:29,667 --> 00:10:32,367
[PHONE RINGING]

179
00:10:32,533 --> 00:10:34,033
Justin, let me do that.

180
00:10:39,367 --> 00:10:40,833
[GRUNTS]

181
00:10:41,600 --> 00:10:44,433
- [BEEPING]
- Luna, answer your phone!

182
00:10:44,933 --> 00:10:47,733
[LINE RINGING]

183
00:10:47,900 --> 00:10:54,933
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

184
00:10:57,733 --> 00:10:59,000
Now what?

185
00:10:59,600 --> 00:11:01,000
Are we just going
to keep digging?

186
00:11:01,933 --> 00:11:03,367
How deep will we go?

187
00:11:03,367 --> 00:11:05,167
We can't give up.

188
00:11:08,267 --> 00:11:13,233
[CELLPHONE RINGING]

189
00:11:13,233 --> 00:11:15,767
Just answer it.
It might be important.

190
00:11:15,767 --> 00:11:18,733
- [CELLPHONE RINGING]
- Alright, give me a minute.

191
00:11:18,733 --> 00:11:22,133
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

192
00:11:22,133 --> 00:11:23,233
[LUNA] Hello?

193
00:11:23,233 --> 00:11:24,967
Hello? [GASPS]

194
00:11:24,967 --> 00:11:27,233
- [CELLPHONE THUDS]
- [GROANS]

195
00:11:27,233 --> 00:11:28,900
- [BODY THUDS]
- [GROANS]

196
00:11:28,900 --> 00:11:30,167
Hello?

197
00:11:30,167 --> 00:11:32,700
[BOTH GRUNTING]

198
00:11:33,900 --> 00:11:34,933
[BLOW LANDS]

199
00:11:34,933 --> 00:11:38,833
[BOTH GRUNTING]

200
00:11:38,833 --> 00:11:40,933
What do you need from me?

201
00:11:40,933 --> 00:11:43,900
- [KICK LANDS]
- [GROANING]

202
00:11:43,933 --> 00:11:45,767
- [GRUNTS]
- [BODY THUDS]

203
00:11:45,767 --> 00:11:50,933
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

204
00:11:50,933 --> 00:11:52,133
Hello?

205
00:11:54,200 --> 00:11:55,400
[LUNA] Hello?

206
00:11:58,100 --> 00:11:59,333
[KNIFE SWISHES]

207
00:12:00,933 --> 00:12:02,733
- [KICK LANDS]
- [GROANS]

208
00:12:08,267 --> 00:12:09,933
Who's that? What do they want?

209
00:12:10,767 --> 00:12:12,933
I don't know... it was weird.

210
00:12:12,933 --> 00:12:14,400
Or maybe they were
prank-calling you?

211
00:12:15,800 --> 00:12:17,100
[SIGHS]

212
00:12:18,700 --> 00:12:20,300
Take a break.
I'll handle this with Justin.

213
00:12:21,300 --> 00:12:23,267
Alright. Thank you.

214
00:12:24,800 --> 00:12:31,767
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

215
00:12:46,733 --> 00:12:53,667
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

216
00:12:56,433 --> 00:13:02,300
[GROANS SOFTLY]

217
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:10,800
[SHOUTING]

218
00:13:11,167 --> 00:13:12,700
- [STABS]
- [GROANS]

219
00:13:13,700 --> 00:13:19,767
- [STABS]
- [GROANING]

220
00:13:19,767 --> 00:13:26,700
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

221
00:13:36,767 --> 00:13:39,800
I told you, you don't
need to come back with me.

222
00:13:39,800 --> 00:13:41,733
You were already
at home, weren't you?

223
00:13:41,733 --> 00:13:45,033
But, Sir...
I still need to help you.

224
00:13:45,033 --> 00:13:46,233
You don't need to.

225
00:13:46,233 --> 00:13:47,767
I can do it on my own, Sari.

226
00:13:47,767 --> 00:13:49,900
I'll just go
to Mt. Arelag myself.

227
00:13:49,900 --> 00:13:51,433
What? Won't I be going with you?

228
00:13:51,433 --> 00:13:54,767
Not anymore. It's dangerous.

229
00:13:54,800 --> 00:13:57,467
- Sir, I've been there before.
- No.

230
00:13:57,467 --> 00:13:59,233
I need you
to stay at the hotel.

231
00:13:59,233 --> 00:14:01,300
Here with our brothers.

232
00:14:01,300 --> 00:14:08,267
[MELANCHOLY MUSIC PLAYING]

233
00:14:16,300 --> 00:14:18,467
Are you sure you have
the right coordinates?

234
00:14:20,167 --> 00:14:21,800
That's what the compass says.

235
00:14:23,833 --> 00:14:26,033
But you know what...
let me check again.

236
00:14:31,133 --> 00:14:32,400
What if...

237
00:14:33,867 --> 00:14:35,267
I flip it around?

238
00:14:35,267 --> 00:14:42,933
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

239
00:14:46,033 --> 00:14:47,433
- [LUNA] Let me see.
- Can you double check?

240
00:14:47,433 --> 00:14:54,567
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

241
00:14:57,833 --> 00:14:59,800
There's another place
that showed up.

242
00:15:00,933 --> 00:15:02,267
Maybe that's why
we're not getting anywhere

243
00:15:02,300 --> 00:15:04,433
because the coordinates
were wrong.

244
00:15:05,200 --> 00:15:07,267
So we dug this for nothing?

245
00:15:07,467 --> 00:15:09,133
We wasted all our
energy for nothing?

246
00:15:09,133 --> 00:15:11,233
That is part of the search.

247
00:15:11,233 --> 00:15:14,033
Let's just remember
why we're doing this.

248
00:15:15,500 --> 00:15:17,133
Justin, be a little patient.

249
00:15:17,567 --> 00:15:19,467
[HUFFS]

250
00:15:19,467 --> 00:15:25,367
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

251
00:15:25,633 --> 00:15:28,000
Where have you been?!
It's late!

252
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:30,500
None of you were
answering my calls!

253
00:15:30,500 --> 00:15:33,033
- And you!
- Sir, get mad at me later!

254
00:15:33,033 --> 00:15:35,333
We have something
important to say.

255
00:15:35,367 --> 00:15:37,567
Martin, please!
You have to listen to us.

256
00:15:37,567 --> 00:15:41,100
Why should I listen to you?
You don't listen to me!

257
00:15:41,100 --> 00:15:43,500
- Brother!
- Martin, please!

258
00:15:43,500 --> 00:15:44,900
[PANTING]

259
00:15:44,900 --> 00:15:47,200
We found out something...

260
00:15:47,200 --> 00:15:50,200
something connected
to Leon's case.

261
00:15:50,200 --> 00:15:52,400
[PANTING]

262
00:15:53,233 --> 00:16:00,167
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

263
00:16:02,267 --> 00:16:04,200
Is this De La Paz?

264
00:16:04,200 --> 00:16:05,867
What does this mean?

265
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:10,100
One of those men kidnapped Juan.

266
00:16:10,133 --> 00:16:12,300
I remember his face, Martin!

267
00:16:12,300 --> 00:16:14,233
I saw his face, I promise!

268
00:16:14,233 --> 00:16:16,100
Trixie is right, Martin.

269
00:16:18,200 --> 00:16:21,533
We followed him, that's why
we ended up in that building.

270
00:16:22,367 --> 00:16:24,267
We believe that...

271
00:16:25,267 --> 00:16:26,900
that's where they took Juan.

272
00:16:28,067 --> 00:16:31,433
So you're saying if De La Paz
is connected to those men,

273
00:16:31,433 --> 00:16:33,400
she's also involved in
what happened to Juan?

274
00:16:33,400 --> 00:16:36,567
Yes. You're right, Martin.

275
00:16:36,567 --> 00:16:39,400
Maybe we can
use this as evidence...

276
00:16:39,400 --> 00:16:42,133
to help Leon get out.

277
00:16:42,167 --> 00:16:43,300
Wait a minute.

278
00:16:43,300 --> 00:16:45,767
If there is a police officer
involved in Juan's case,

279
00:16:45,767 --> 00:16:48,433
it means that Leon isn't safe.

280
00:16:48,433 --> 00:16:50,633
- Is Gio back yet?
- No, sir.

281
00:16:51,300 --> 00:16:54,733
Call Kiko. I'll call Gio.
We need to tell everyone!

282
00:16:54,733 --> 00:16:56,267
I'll call Justin.

283
00:16:56,267 --> 00:16:59,600
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

284
00:17:02,500 --> 00:17:06,433
- [COFFEE POURING]
- [SIGHING, SNIFFLING]

285
00:17:08,933 --> 00:17:10,700
Morning, bud. [SIGHS]

286
00:17:12,300 --> 00:17:13,400
What?

287
00:17:13,500 --> 00:17:16,100
Are you down
for some barbecue later?

288
00:17:18,500 --> 00:17:19,633
Barbecue?

289
00:17:20,867 --> 00:17:22,500
What do you mean barbecue?

290
00:17:23,333 --> 00:17:26,433
Isn't it too early
for some barbecue?

291
00:17:26,533 --> 00:17:28,800
Not now. For lunch!

292
00:17:28,967 --> 00:17:31,067
We haven't had some
for a while now.

293
00:17:31,533 --> 00:17:32,733
[RUSTLES]

294
00:17:33,167 --> 00:17:35,900
Are you asking to have barbecue
'cause you don't have a meeting?

295
00:17:36,467 --> 00:17:38,467
I have some documents
I have to sign but,

296
00:17:38,633 --> 00:17:39,733
you know, that can wait.

297
00:17:39,833 --> 00:17:42,333
For now, I want to...

298
00:17:42,467 --> 00:17:44,567
just hang out with you.
Spend time together.

299
00:17:44,667 --> 00:17:47,600
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

300
00:17:47,700 --> 00:17:50,300
[ANDY CLICKS TONGUE] Okay.
Alright. I get it, look.

301
00:17:51,833 --> 00:17:53,333
I forgive you.

302
00:17:56,000 --> 00:17:57,300
For what?

303
00:17:59,667 --> 00:18:01,533
Because you doubted me.

304
00:18:02,733 --> 00:18:03,767
When...

305
00:18:03,867 --> 00:18:05,767
you confronted me by asking me

306
00:18:05,867 --> 00:18:07,500
what I'm doing to the Almazans.

307
00:18:07,667 --> 00:18:10,800
And uh, why they are
so mad at me.

308
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:15,667
Dad, I didn't confront you.

309
00:18:17,300 --> 00:18:18,667
I was just asking you.

310
00:18:19,233 --> 00:18:20,333
[CLICKS TONGUE]

311
00:18:20,500 --> 00:18:22,833
To-may-to, to-mah-to,
it's all the same, but...

312
00:18:23,567 --> 00:18:25,567
it's done, you know?
Forget about it.

313
00:18:27,400 --> 00:18:30,067
What? You down
for a barbecue lunch?

314
00:18:30,200 --> 00:18:36,333
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

315
00:18:36,500 --> 00:18:37,567
Okay.

316
00:18:37,833 --> 00:18:39,133
[ANDY] Alright. Good.

317
00:18:40,233 --> 00:18:41,867
Mom said she'll update us.

318
00:18:42,033 --> 00:18:43,733
- She's still with Leon.
- [RATTLES]

319
00:18:45,033 --> 00:18:46,567
So, Attorney,

320
00:18:46,867 --> 00:18:49,400
can we use that to free Leon?

321
00:18:50,067 --> 00:18:51,400
The only thing this could prove

322
00:18:51,533 --> 00:18:54,533
is De La Paz's association
with the kidnappers.

323
00:18:55,233 --> 00:18:58,033
But that doesn't mean
that she kidnapped

324
00:18:58,200 --> 00:18:59,933
or killed Juan.

325
00:19:00,433 --> 00:19:03,667
How can we prove
that they're the kidnappers?

326
00:19:05,533 --> 00:19:07,200
Then is this video useless?

327
00:19:07,867 --> 00:19:09,367
[LAWYER] Hm, we could...

328
00:19:09,467 --> 00:19:12,100
question Juan's sworn statement.

329
00:19:12,233 --> 00:19:16,000
Since it's made by De La Paz,

330
00:19:16,100 --> 00:19:18,367
who is connected
to the kidnappers.

331
00:19:18,467 --> 00:19:20,167
But that's as far as it goes.

332
00:19:20,533 --> 00:19:22,367
[JUSTIN] If we can't pin
that police officer,

333
00:19:22,467 --> 00:19:24,667
then we also can't pin
Uncle Andy?

334
00:19:25,300 --> 00:19:26,367
That's right.

335
00:19:26,467 --> 00:19:29,900
But still, the strongest
evidence we could have

336
00:19:30,100 --> 00:19:31,733
is if we have a video

337
00:19:31,833 --> 00:19:34,100
or a witness who can say

338
00:19:34,267 --> 00:19:38,133
that it was De La Paz, or Andy,
or whoever it is

339
00:19:38,267 --> 00:19:41,200
killed Juan and not Leon.

340
00:19:41,300 --> 00:19:43,433
But we have a good chance
don't we, Attorney?

341
00:19:43,600 --> 00:19:45,600
We already have a CCTV footage
from Hotel 88,

342
00:19:45,767 --> 00:19:47,233
we have witnesses too.

343
00:19:47,967 --> 00:19:50,900
And if they can't prove
Juan's sworn statement,

344
00:19:51,067 --> 00:19:52,800
we can get Leon
out of prison, right?

345
00:19:53,300 --> 00:19:54,733
That's what we'll present
to them.

346
00:19:54,900 --> 00:20:01,733
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

347
00:20:04,300 --> 00:20:06,467
[SIGHS] You know, bud...

348
00:20:06,633 --> 00:20:09,567
[CLEARS THROAT]
ever since your mom died,

349
00:20:10,533 --> 00:20:11,900
there are only
three things in this world

350
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:13,400
that I would do.

351
00:20:13,500 --> 00:20:17,400
Business, fishing,
and taking care of you.

352
00:20:18,500 --> 00:20:21,167
Dad, how did we get here
from talking about barbecue?

353
00:20:22,367 --> 00:20:23,500
How did we get to death?

354
00:20:23,633 --> 00:20:26,667
We're not talking about death
per se,

355
00:20:26,800 --> 00:20:29,633
just that the bottom line
of what I'm saying

356
00:20:29,800 --> 00:20:34,067
is that everything I do
is for you. Okay?

357
00:20:34,833 --> 00:20:37,667
So, when I say we're gonna have
a barbecue lunch,

358
00:20:38,333 --> 00:20:39,867
just let me have it.

359
00:20:40,000 --> 00:20:44,633
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

360
00:20:44,733 --> 00:20:45,633
Thanks, Dad.

361
00:20:45,733 --> 00:20:46,867
You're welcome.

362
00:20:55,033 --> 00:20:56,367
[SIPS]

363
00:20:59,367 --> 00:21:00,933
[EDWARD] I want
to believe you, Dad.

364
00:21:01,900 --> 00:21:03,300
<i> I really do.</i>

365
00:21:03,900 --> 00:21:10,700
[GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

366
00:21:12,533 --> 00:21:13,733
[KIKO] We couldn't pin it
on De La Paz,

367
00:21:13,867 --> 00:21:15,667
but at least we now know
that she's in cahoots with them.

368
00:21:15,833 --> 00:21:17,367
We're on the right track, right?

369
00:21:17,533 --> 00:21:18,567
Yes.

370
00:21:18,700 --> 00:21:21,233
Apart from the kidnappers
you and Trixie saw,

371
00:21:21,367 --> 00:21:22,867
there could be more
accomplices.

372
00:21:24,700 --> 00:21:27,467
Aren't we reporting De La Paz
to the police?

373
00:21:28,000 --> 00:21:29,733
[GIO] What if the other police
are involved too?

374
00:21:29,867 --> 00:21:31,533
You're suspicious of Sir Henry?

375
00:21:31,700 --> 00:21:33,733
With all that's happening,
everyone is suspicious.

376
00:21:33,867 --> 00:21:37,533
In my opinion,
we can trust Sir Henry.

377
00:21:38,867 --> 00:21:41,333
He helped us
when Roi took Jake.

378
00:21:42,233 --> 00:21:43,933
If there's an accomplice
within their ranks,

379
00:21:44,733 --> 00:21:46,333
there should be an ally too.

380
00:21:46,433 --> 00:21:53,333
- [STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]
- [FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

381
00:22:06,800 --> 00:22:08,433
I agree with Kiko.

382
00:22:09,233 --> 00:22:12,200
We can report or talk
to Sir Henry.

383
00:22:12,300 --> 00:22:13,533
Justin.

384
00:22:13,700 --> 00:22:15,267
- Let's go talk to him.
- [GIO] No.

385
00:22:15,433 --> 00:22:20,267
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

386
00:22:20,433 --> 00:22:22,600
My brothers and I will do it.

387
00:22:23,967 --> 00:22:27,267
[SIGHS] But what if he's also
not trustworthy?

388
00:22:28,467 --> 00:22:30,233
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

389
00:22:30,600 --> 00:22:31,900
We'll take the risk.

390
00:22:34,267 --> 00:22:35,433
We'll take care of it.

391
00:22:35,600 --> 00:22:42,600
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

392
00:22:49,800 --> 00:22:50,800
[MONETTE] Do you have
my spray bottle?

393
00:22:50,967 --> 00:22:52,400
[RAPHIE] Yeah. It's here.

394
00:22:52,500 --> 00:22:53,767
[MONETTE SIGHS]

395
00:22:53,933 --> 00:22:55,000
[RAPHIE COUGHS, SNIFFS]

396
00:22:55,133 --> 00:22:57,600
[RAPHIE] My god!
It's a real mess in here.

397
00:22:57,967 --> 00:23:00,933
Oh my-- Can we handle this?

398
00:23:01,333 --> 00:23:03,667
What's with all
this litter and stuff?

399
00:23:06,200 --> 00:23:07,967
- What just happened here?
- [SPRAYING]

400
00:23:08,133 --> 00:23:10,133
Monette, I still can't get
over it.

401
00:23:10,300 --> 00:23:11,600
[MONETTE] With what?

402
00:23:12,300 --> 00:23:14,267
[RAPHIE GROANS] That police
officer is unbelievable.

403
00:23:14,433 --> 00:23:15,733
I thought she's sensible.

404
00:23:17,467 --> 00:23:19,800
That De La Paz even went here
lots of times.

405
00:23:19,967 --> 00:23:22,133
I even welcomed her warmly.

406
00:23:22,833 --> 00:23:25,633
Turns out she's involved
with Juan's death!

407
00:23:25,733 --> 00:23:27,500
[RAPHIE] Oh, when I heard
her voice

408
00:23:27,667 --> 00:23:29,433
from the place
where they kept Juan,

409
00:23:29,533 --> 00:23:31,467
I got chills all over!

410
00:23:31,567 --> 00:23:32,933
I recognized her voice
right away.

411
00:23:33,033 --> 00:23:36,000
Plus she talked
to Juan's kidnappers

412
00:23:36,167 --> 00:23:38,300
as if they were her buddies!

413
00:23:39,333 --> 00:23:42,333
So sometimes even the police
can't be trusted.

414
00:23:42,833 --> 00:23:44,967
Even those close
to the Almazans,

415
00:23:45,133 --> 00:23:48,967
like Sir Andy can't be trusted.
What more other people?

416
00:23:49,633 --> 00:23:50,800
But...

417
00:23:50,900 --> 00:23:54,000
do you think De La Paz
and Sir Andy are in cahoots

418
00:23:54,167 --> 00:23:55,600
with what happened to Juan?

419
00:23:55,733 --> 00:23:57,300
[RAPHIE] We still need
more evidence.

420
00:23:57,400 --> 00:23:59,800
[SIGHS] But everyone
already thinks so.

421
00:23:59,900 --> 00:24:01,833
It's just difficult to prove.

422
00:24:02,833 --> 00:24:04,867
- Well, let's see.
- [RAPHIE CLICKS TONGUE]

423
00:24:05,833 --> 00:24:09,000
But, Raphie,
can we handle all this?

424
00:24:09,667 --> 00:24:12,500
[RAPHIE] I don't think
I can handle lifting all this...

425
00:24:15,833 --> 00:24:18,133
<i>Who did you work with
in killing Juan Soliman?</i>

426
00:24:18,233 --> 00:24:19,233
<i> This is not just Andy's work.</i>

427
00:24:19,367 --> 00:24:21,833
<i>I'm certain he's working
with someone powerful</i>

428
00:24:21,933 --> 00:24:23,467
<i>- to keep me locked up.
- An accomplice?</i>

429
00:24:25,067 --> 00:24:27,167
<i>Excuse me,
please leave this area.</i>

430
00:24:29,233 --> 00:24:31,333
<i>Don't talk to me anymore,
don't see me anymore.</i>

431
00:24:31,433 --> 00:24:32,767
<i> We can't meet ever again.</i>

432
00:24:32,900 --> 00:24:34,533
<i>We have a different offer
for you.</i>

433
00:24:34,633 --> 00:24:36,433
<i>- What is it?
- Clues.</i>

434
00:24:36,567 --> 00:24:38,400
<i> About the hidden treasure.</i>
